[Nouns] whole, totality, integrity; totalness; entirety, ensemble, collectiveness; unity [more]; completeness [more]; indivisibility, indiscerptibility; integration, embodiment; integer.
all, the whole, total, aggregate, one and all, gross amount, sum, sum total, tout ensemble, length and breadth of, Alpha and Omega, "be all and end all"; complex, complexus; lock stock and barrel.
bulk, mass, lump, tissue, staple, body, compages; trunk, torso, bole, hull, hulk, skeleton, greater part, major part, best part, principal part, main part; essential part (importance) [more]; lion's share, Benjamin's mess; the long and the short; nearly, all, almost all.
[Verbs] form a whole, constitute a whole; integrate, embody, amass; aggregate (assemble) [more]; amount to, come to.
[Adjectives] whole, total, integral, entire; complete [more]; one, individual.
unbroken, uncut, undivided, unsevered, unclipped, uncropped, unshorn; seamless; undiminished; undemolished, undissolved, undestroyed, unbruised.
indivisible, indissoluble, indissolvable, indiscerptible.
wholesale, sweeping; comprehensive.
[Adverbs] wholly, altogether; totally (completely) [more]; entirely, all, all in all, wholesale, in a body, collectively, all put together; in the aggregate, in the lump, in the mass, in the gross, in the main, in the long run; en masse, on the whole, bodily, en bloc, in extenso, throughout, every inch; substantially.
